# Cursor Rules — AI Lab Template

## Architecture
- **Backend**: NestJS 10 + TypeORM + PostgreSQL — `apps/backend/src/`
- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript strict — `apps/frontend/`
- **AI**: shared package at `packages/ai-core/` — use `generateText()` from there
- **Automations**: n8n workflows in `n8n-workflows/*.json`
- Docs & rules: `docs/AGENTS.md` — read it for full conventions

## Before every edit
1. Read the full target file first
2. Check `docs/AGENTS.md` for relevant conventions
3. Never edit more than one file per logical change unless necessary

## Code style — Backend (NestJS/TypeScript)
- Guards: `JwtAuthGuard` for JWT, `JwtOrWebhookSecretGuard` for n8n endpoints
- n8n endpoints always check `req.webhookAuth` flag to skip user ownership
- DTOs require `class-validator` decorators on every field
- Services inject dependencies via constructor, never static methods
- Always use `this.logger.warn()` for external API errors, never `console.error`
- Wrap ALL external HTTP calls (Telegram, AI providers) in try/catch

## Code style — Frontend (Next.js)
- All API calls go via `lib/checklists.ts` — never raw `fetch()` in components
- Async handlers: `async function handleX() {}` called as `() => void handleX()`
- State: one `useState` per concept — no mega-state objects
- Pages > 200 lines: extract step/section components to `components/*/` subfolders
- No `localStorage` direct access — use `useAuth` hook

## n8n workflows
- HTTP credential ID: `EfBrBbQ88fwJlS4R` ("Header Auth account")
- Telegram credential ID: `8JyddEiApG6k1J3x` ("Telegram account")
- Always use `$env.BACKEND_PUBLIC_URL` — never `$vars.`
- Callback data format: `"action:checklistId:itemId"`

## What NOT to do
- Never add `any` types
- Never hardcode secrets or API keys
- Never use `$vars.` in n8n (use `$env.`)
- Never bypass TypeScript with `@ts-ignore`
- Never commit `.env` files
- Never write inline `<style>` — use Tailwind classes only
- Never put business logic in controllers — only in services

## File size limits
- Pages: max 300 lines → split into components
- Components: max 250 lines → split into sub-components
- Services: max 500 lines → split into focused services

## Env vars
- New vars → add to `.env.example` + `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`
- Backend: `this.configService.get<string>('VAR', 'default')`
- Frontend public: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` prefix
- Never log actual values — log `!!process.env.VAR` only

## Commit messages
`type(scope): description`  
Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, chore, test  
Example: `fix(n8n): align credential IDs in workflow 02`
